Meet <b>Denisyasha</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Denisyasha has lived in Metro Park since January 7, 2005, and loves her neighborhood. Her home at <a href='/home/?user=booise'>25801 Broadway Boulevard</a> is just a hop, skip, and a jump from <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/hallway.phtml">Millsberry Academy</a> and the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/arcade.phtml">arcade</a>, two places where she spends a lot of her time.<br><br>She's a real whiz at the games in the arcade, and is constantly trying to best her high scores. She even thinks that some of the games have helped her in school. The challenge of <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=240">Millsberry Hide & Seek</a> has improved her reflexes and observation skills, which has helped her with everything from gym class to math problems! <br><br>But more than playing games, Denisyasha loves to write. She first got interested in writing after spending a summer reading as many books as she could. <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=2">Bookends Bookshop</a> owner Carla Robbins got to know her by name, and recommended many different titles for her. Now Denisyasha's mind is full of ideas for her own stories, which she jots down and keeps in a binder in her room. <br><br>When she's not setting records in the arcade, studying, or dreaming about being a bestselling novelist, she's often in the Millsberry Academy <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/gym/">gym</a> playing sports or cheering on her friends. This girl is not short on school spirit!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Denisyasha, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
